    • Method Detail

      • delta

        public abstract java.lang.String delta(char c,
                                       char p)
        This abstract method determines and returns the next state of automaton for given char inputs.
        Parameters:
        c - Input string's next char.
        p - Char that poped from stack.
        Returns:
        Finds valid transition by given inputs. If no transition, null returns.

      • accept

        public boolean accept(java.lang.String w,
                      char init)
        This method checks the input string for automaton and prints result step by step. Also, if input is accepted, returns true. If not, returns false.
        Parameters:
        w - Input to check if it's accepted by automaton and print.
        init - Initial char to push into stack.
        Returns:
        Checks string. If accepted, true returns. If not, false returns.
